CS380P Project  Samuel Palmer and Joe Elizondo

=============================================================
Building Our Project:
=============================================================

The current version of our code compiles and runs with version 1.1 of the Chapel compiler.
Our project currently builds on the UTCS machines with the following Chapel variables:

CHPL_HOST_PLATFORM: linux32
CHPL_HOST_COMPILER: gnu
CHPL_TARGET_PLATFORM: linux32
CHPL_TARGET_COMPILER: gnu
CHPL_COMM: gasnet
  CHPL_COMM_SUBSTRATE: udp
  CHPL_GASNET_SEGMENT: everything
CHPL_TASKS: fifo
CHPL_THREADS: pthreads
CHPL_LAUNCHER: amudprun
CHPL_TIMERS: generic
CHPL_MEM: default
CHPL_MAKE: make

The shared memory portion of our code compiles and runs on TACC's Ranger cluster with the following Chapel variables:

CHPL_HOST_PLATFORM: linux64
CHPL_HOST_COMPILER: gnu
CHPL_TARGET_PLATFORM: linux64
CHPL_TARGET_COMPILER: gnu
CHPL_COMM: none
CHPL_TASKS: fifo
CHPL_THREADS: pthreads
CHPL_LAUNCHER: none
CHPL_TIMERS: generic
CHPL_MEM: default
CHPL_MAKE: gmake



The following make targets are defined in our makefile:
parallel      (Compiles our project with the --fast compiler flag. Outputs "flame_parallel" and "flame_parallel_real")
serial        (Compiles our project with the --serial and --fast compiler flags. Outputs "flame_serial" and "flame_serial_real")
all           (Builds "parallel" and "serial" targets. This is the default target.)
clean         (Removes "flame_parallel" "flame_parallel_real" "flame_serial" and "flame_serial_real")



=============================================================
Running Our Project:
=============================================================

To run our project you must specify the following parameters on the command line:
--Afile A_matrix.txt
--Bfile B_matrix.txt
--blkSize [int]    (specifies the block size for the blocked GEMM)
-nl [int]          (specifies the number of locales)

The following parameter is optional:
--answer answer_matrix.txt   (specifies the file to write the result matrix. Defaults to "answer")

Examples:
./flame_parallel --Afile testmatrixA100x100.txt --Bfile testmatrixB100x100.txt --answer answer.txt --blkSize 10 -nl 2
./flame_serial --Afile testmatrixA100x100.txt --Bfile testmatrixB100x100.txt --answer answer.txt --blkSize 10 -nl 2


Where testmatrixA100x100.txt and testmatrixB100x100.txt have the following structure (excluding the comments):
m n
1 2 3 4 ... n        <===========  row 1 of the matrix
. 
. 
.
1 2 3 4 ... n        <===========  row m of the matrix





